5|$|<b>The</b> <b>Methodist</b> Church in the town's High Street {{celebrated its}} 150th Anniversary in 2009. In 1746, John Wesley's {{travelling}} preachers, based in Bristol were invited in the mid-1700s {{to support the}} local society, the man himself first coming in 1767. By {{the middle of the}} 1800s, the congregation had outgrown the original chapel erected in 1775 in Rackvernal Road (now demolished). In the 1990s, the present church building and adjoining hall were totally refurbished and linked, the facilities being well used by the local community. Local Methodists are part of the Bristol District of <b>the</b> <b>Methodist</b> Church and in the North East Somerset & Bath Circuit.|$|E
